FT  27 AUG 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Australian wool market drifted down a little from last week's slightly
firmer levels, although again there was very little change in prices in
terms of the local currency. Of dominant importance outside Australia was
weakness in that currency against the US dollar, and the renewed weakness in
the US dollar itself. Wool therefore again became cheaper to buy for
practically all overseas users. The situation involves slow and very
competitive trading throughout the trade. Recession continues to play a
part, as do the final days of the main European holiday season.
