<HEADLINE>
FT  27 AUG 92 / UK Company News: BTR to buy Pirelli's Brazilian offshoot
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BTR, the industrial holding company, is buying Getoflex Metzeler, the
Brazilian industrial rubber product business, from Pirelli of Italy for
about Pounds 10m cash.
In 1991 Getoflex, which has three factories in Sao Paulo, incurred an
operating loss of Pounds 800,000 on sales of Pounds 24m. Net assets being
acquired amount to Pounds 22m.
BTR has also completed on schedule the acquisition of Pirelli's European
sealing and anti-vibration businesses following clearance from the EC.
