<HEADLINE>
FT  27 AUG 92 / UK Company News: Sleepy Kids deeper loss after provision
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sleepy Kids, the USM-quoted co-producer of Potsworth &amp; Co and other
animation and character merchandising, incurred an increased pre-tax loss of
Pounds 109,000 for the six months to April 30, against Pounds 62,000.
The outcome this time was after an exceptional charge of Pounds 69,000
representing a provision against income receivable from Hanna-Barbera.
The company also said it planned to raise up to Pounds 301,000 in a private
placing. A maximum of 4.3m new ordinary shares will be placed at 7p per
share by Shaw &amp; Co with a limited number of institutional and other
investors.
Turnover fell to Pounds 80,000 (Pounds 110,000) and there was an operating
loss of Pounds 50,000 (Pounds 91,000). Losses per share came through at
0.55p (0.38p).
Sleepy Kids has exercised an option for a sole and exclusive worldwide
licence for the intellectual property rights (excluding certain book rights)
over the Budgie character, already well known from the children's books
written by the Duchess of York.
</TEXT>
