   By RAYMOND HUGHES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A MAN appeared at Bow Street magistrates court yesterday charged by the
Serious Fraud Office with corruption in connection with a contract tender to
provide pipes for the Channel tunnel, Raymond Hughes writes.
Mr Thomas East, former procurement supervisor with H and G Engineering, a UK
process engineering and management contractor, was remanded on conditional
bail until September 23. He was ordered to be held in custody until he could
produce sureties totalling Pounds 400,000.
The charge against Mr East alleges that, on a day before June 25 1991, he
