FT  27 AUG 92 / Refit drill
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BETHAN HUTTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The North Sea Pioneer rig is transported by the Mighty Servant 1, a
semi-submersible ship, into the port of Dundee, Tayside, for structural
reinforcing work at MacGregor Engineering, Bethan Hutton writes.
The rig, which was operated in the North Sea by Hamilton Brothers, the US
oil company, is to be used as a floating production facility by the Ghana
National Petroleum Corporation off Angola.
The Mighty Servant 1 is operated by Wijsmuller Transport of the Netherlands.
Its main deck can be lowered under the water, allowing a rig to be moved on
top. The procedure is a fairly routine one internationally but it is the
first time an oil rig has entered Dundee on top of a ship rather than being
towed behind one.
