<HEADLINE>
FT  26 AUG 92 / The Lex Column: HSBC
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Yesterday's interim figures from the Hongkong Bank underline that strong
Pacific operations are likely to set it apart from the pack. Asset growth in
the Far East is running at an annual rate of 13 per cent, and the return on
assets remains respectable. There are still some lingering doubts about the
extent of provisioning for Olympia &amp; York, but loan losses across the group
appear to be under control despite the influx of new business in Hong Kong.
Even so, pro forma consolidation of Midland shows just how dilutive the
acquisition will be: earnings per share fall from 21p to 14.4p on
consolidation, and the tier I capital ratio drops from 9.4 per cent to 6.4
per cent.
