<HEADLINE>
FT  26 AUG 92 / International Company News: Bank of Montreal ahead 14%
despite provisions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BANK of Montreal, Canada's third largest bank, reported a 14 per cent gain
in third-quarter profit despite higher loan loss provisions.
Net income for the July 31 quarter was CDollars 173m (USDollars 89m), or
CDollars 1.29 a share, up from CDollars 152m, or CDollars 1.17 a share, a
year earlier. This reflected improving market share, strong treasury and
international operations and tight cost control.
Net interest income was up 16 per cent. Return on common equity was 15.1 per
cent.
Despite the recession, small and medium-sized business loans were up 15 per
cent and consumer mortgages up 17 per cent. Growth in US corporate business
continued good.
Foreign exchange trading revenues gained 18 per cent and a CDollars 7m
dividend was received from the Brazilian subsidiary. Expenses were held to a
5 per cent increase.
Nine month earnings were CDollars 480m, or CDollars 3.59 a share, against
CDollars 419m, or CDollars 3.28, a year earlier. Average assets were
CDollars 103bn against CDollars 93bn.
Non-performing loans totalled CDollars 2.1bn, or 3.2 per cent of total
loans, up CDollars 318m from April 30.
</TEXT>
